Usage: btoep-list-ranges [options]
Display all ranges present or missing within a dataset.

Options:
--help                     Display this information.
--version                  Display the version of this tool.
--dataset=<name>           Name (or path) of the dataset.
--index-path=<path>        Use this index file instead of the default one.
--lockfile-path=<path>     Use this lock file instead of the default one. This
                           is dangerous.
--range-format=<format>    Display ranges in the given format. Possible values:
                           - incl (default):
                             Display ranges as "a..b", where b is inclusive.
                           - excl:
                             Display ranges as "a...b", where b is exclusive.
--missing                  Display missing ranges instead of existing ranges.
